place.name: FRAMINGHAM EARL
place.gazetteerText: FRAMINGHAM-EARL, a parish in Henstead district, Norfolk, 3¾ miles ENE of Swainsthorpe r. station, and 4¾ SE of Norwich. It has a post office under Norwich. Acres, 560. Real property, £1, 218. Pop., 136. Houses, 30. The property is divided. Framingham House is a chief residence. The living is a rectory, annexed to the rectory of Bixley, in the diocese of Norwich. The church is Norman; has a round tower; and was repaired in 1858. There are a Wesleyan chapel, a national school, and a fuel allotment. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
